---
description: Invokes before-commit-guard when user runs git commit (pre-commit hook) or fixes a failed commit. Also when editing pre-commit or lint-staged config.
globs: .husky/pre-commit, package.json
alwaysApply: false
---

When any of the following happen, read and follow the **before-commit-guard** skill:

1. **User runs `git commit`** — The Husky pre-commit hook (`.husky/pre-commit`) runs the guard. If the user reports that the commit was rejected or pre-commit failed, invoke the skill to diagnose and fix the failing step (lint, typecheck, validate:domain, gitleaks, conflict markers, large files).

2. **User asks to fix commit errors / make code commit-ready / fix pre-commit** — Run the guard checks (`pnpm validate`, `pnpm validate:domain`) and fix any failures per the skill.

3. **Pre-commit or lint-staged config is modified** — When `.husky/pre-commit` or `package.json` (lint-staged) is created or modified, read `.cursor/skills/before-commit-guard/SKILL.md` and ensure the hook steps and this skill stay in sync.

Skill file: `.cursor/skills/before-commit-guard/SKILL.md`
